            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": ">  tree-sitter does support only context-free grammars. \n\nTo be clear: context-free grammar after custom preprocessing in per language scanner.c . even very common languages like python and html depend on this. \n\n>  impossible to handle without external tools like compilers or languages servers (with language-specific extensions).\n\nThis is the expected trade-off. LSP can also provide highlights as semantic tokens and refactors as code actions. it is more expensive/higher latency than tree-sitter but then you can do whatever you want completely unconstrained by any parser design.",
