        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> This is the expected trade-off. LSP can also provide highlights as semantic tokens and refactors as code actions. it is more expensive/higher latency than tree-sitter but then you can do whatever you want completely unconstrained by any parser design.\n\nThe thing is that there are plugins which rely on tree-sitter-produced CST to provide motions and stuff; as long as there is nothing else in core, those plugins are not going to get integrated with other ways of getting CST which is quite sad.\n\nWell, I think hijacking tree-sitter-related functions might work, so I'll try to pull it off as a plugin then.\n\nUPD: Well, if something else is in core then we have two kinds of plugins with similar purposes, so I kinda see the problem",
